results.name: Final term of n-th row of A077664.
comment: a(p) = 2p+1, p is a prime. a(2^n) = 3*2^n -1.

a(n) also equals the (n+phi(n))th integer from among those positive integers coprime to n, where phi(n) = A000010(n). a(n) also equals n + (the n-th integer from among those positive integers coprime to n) = n + A069213(n). - _Leroy Quet_, Apr 12 2007
link: Reinhard Zumkeller, Table of n, a(n) for n = 1..1000
